jk","Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1433–":"about 1483–Deceased","1420–1510":"1420–1510","1467–1556":"1467–1556","1483–Female":"1483–Deceased","1556":"1556","1467":"1467","1510":"1510","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","Abt 1433":"about 1483","Abt 1504":"about 1504",", Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Knightley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Knightley (Staffs)."],"variants":[{"name":"Knightly","meanings":["English (Middlesex and Cambridgeshire): variant of <b>Knightley</b>, a habitational name from Knightley in Gnosall (Staffordshire). The placename derives from Old English <i>cniht</i> ‘knight, young man, retainer’ (genitive plural <i>cnihta</i>) + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. This is the usual spelling of the name in Ireland, where it has been establishes since the 17th century."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Knightley was born about 1483, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Richard Brailes about 1504, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1433–":"umbes 1483–Surnud","1420–1510":"1420–1510","1467–1556":"1467–1556","1483–Female":"1483–Surnud","1556":"1556","1467":"1467","1510":"1510","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","Abt 1433":"umbes 1483","Abt 1504":"umbes 1504",", Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1433–":"noin 1483–Kuollut","1420–1510":"1420–1510","1467–1556":"1467–1556","1483–Female":"1483–Kuollut","1556":"1556","1467":"1467","1510":"1510","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","Abt 1433":"noin 1483","Abt 1504":"noin 1504",", Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1433–":"environ 1483–Décédée","1420–1510":"1420–1510","1467–1556":"1467–1556","1483–Female":"1483–Décédée","1556":"1556","1467":"1467","1510":"1510","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","Abt 1433":"environ 1483","Abt 1504":"environ 1504",", Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Northampton, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Knightley est née environ 1483, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Richard Brailes environ 1504, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1433–":"um 1483–Verstorben","1420–1510":"1420–1510","1467–1556":"1